    <p>Burdman Electric of Fort Worth, TX is a residential and light commercial electrician with a 2.9 star reputation. Despite positive testimonials on platforms like Yelp, several customers report long wait times, inconsistent communication, and unexpected billing. Michael, the listed operator, is noted to be knowledgeable but often unavailable during critical job phases. One customer said, “He was nice, but we waited two weeks for a panel install and got no updates.”</p>

    <p>According to multiple reports, Burdman Electric frequently underestimates project timelines. One job that was expected to take a day extended to nearly a week without written notice or explanation. Michael reportedly works with subcontractors, which sometimes leads to mixed outcomes. While the final product is often acceptable, the journey there can be rocky for homeowners who value promptness and updates.</p>

